17/09/2003
ZAGREB, Croatia -- Prime Minister Ivica Racan met with his Bulgarian counterpart, Simeon Saxe-Coburg, on Tuesday (16 September) after the opening of the International Fair in Zagreb. The two discussed bilateral ties and opportunities for co-operation, especially in trade and tourism. They also agreed on the need for development of infrastructure and transport links in Southeast Europe.
In other news Tuesday, Bulgarian European Affairs Minister Meglena Kouneva met with the prime minister of Luxembourg, Jean-Claude Juncker, who pledged his country's support for Bulgaria's efforts to join the EU. (BTA, BNT, BNR, Croatian Radio - 16/09/03)
